'''Otto Bagman''' was a [[Wizardkind|wizard]] and brother of [[Ludovic Bagman|Ludo Bagman]]. He got into trouble with a [[magic]]al [[lawn mower|lawnmower]], a [[Non-magic people|Muggle]] artefact. [[Arthur Weasley]] helped him sort out the problem, and as thanks, his brother Ludo provided the [[Weasley family]] with tickets to the [[1994]] [[Quidditch World Cup]] final.<ref name="GOF5">{{GOF|B|5}}</ref>

==Etymology==
"Otto" is a later German form of Audo or [[Odo]], originally a short form of various names beginning with the Germanic element od meaning "wealth, fortune".

